00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: Sorry to bother you while you're tired, but it looks
like your "comrade from the same squad" you mentioned came
in as you were leaving, and was here until just a moment
ago.
Is that true...!?
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: From what I heard about what they did, they said the
same thing as you, so it's probably no mistake.
So, what was their condition like!?
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: They weren't injured to the point of death, but
that's just it. As you imagined, they were in a terrible
state.

Akane: You seem relieved, but then why do you think they're
not here?

That is... perhaps they finished their punishment and were
sent back to the communal living area?
00_st_akane01_anger
Akane: That would be nice, wouldn't it?
Akane: I'll tell you exactly what I saw.
回想シーン。黒ずくめの男たちに連れて行かれる室長。

Akane: Someone came. It was that guy who occasionally comes
here to trade the crystals mined from this place.

Akane: I've only caught a glimpse of him before, but there's
no mistake. The guard and that guy exchanged a few words,
then took your comrade away.

Akane: Along with several other workers who had been used up
and broken down here, no longer able to do proper work,
practically like walking corpses.
00_st_akane01_anger

Akane: That was clearly a vile trade-off for those who can
no longer serve as laborers.

Akane: It's something if even half the promises made here
are kept.
00_st_akane01_nomal
Akane: Disappointed you couldn't reunite?
If they're alive, that's good enough for me, that's...
00_st_akane01_anger

Akane: You seem to have convinced yourself and stopped
thinking about it, but just like your important person,
today and tomorrow someone else will be sacrificed like
trash here.

Akane: As time goes by, people disappear and you stop
feeling anything. You kill your heart and give up on living.
That's how disposable laborers who are only alive in name
are made.

Akane: Escaping from pain is the smart way to get by here.
It's pointless to tell you not to worry about it now,
though.
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: It might be tough now, but we never know when we'll
be able to meet like this again. There's a message I have to
tell you. It's from your important comrade.

Room Manager: So that's it, they went to the boss... Sold
themselves for me... That guy is really naive, serious to a
fault, and an idiot.
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: Reisha was praying for your safety. I can't do much,
but I can at least pass on a message.

Room Manager: Come to think of it, I didn't ask for her
name. So her name is Reisha, that girl.
00_st_akane01_nomal
Akane: ...

Room Manager: You should always put yourself first. That's
what I've been chanting and living by all this time...
Room Manager: ...

Room Manager: I've lived a terrible life up until now. It's
only natural I ended up thrown in here. So I accepted living
here and thought it'd be fine to just whittle away and die
off quietly.

Room Manager: In the midst of such days, one day I took care
of an injured person who was brought in.

Room Manager: There were no special feelings involved; it
was my role so I provided care. The conversation was also
just a brief comfort. But on a whim, that person thanked me.
Even though they were far more broken than me.

Room Manager: Sweet, naive, and straightforward. At first, I
was just teasing them.

Room Manager: But as I watched them trying to live their way
even in this scum-like place, trying to be strong while
carrying their weakness, such a naive aspiration...

Room Manager: Just a little bit, I felt like facing my own
way of life that I held in my hands. Uncharacteristically
so.

Room Manager: I guess it was because I was aware that my
time was running short. She was too dazzling for a place
like the bottom of this pit.

Room Manager: I know it's too late now, but I've been
thinking... maybe I can atone, even just a little, for what
I've done to others in the past, for those within my reach
who went unrewarded.
00_st_akane01_serious

Akane: So it's self-sacrifice, huh? Who do you think would
admire that? It's stupid.
Akane: ...You're selfish, you know.

Room Manager: I know. While saying it's for someone else's
sake, in the end, I'm just trying to stick to my own way of
life. That's what it means.

Room Manager: But there's only so much a powerless person
can do.

Room Manager: I felt like I had accomplished something by
getting hurt while protecting someone else, but even now,
I'm being helped by that person who I kept telling to only
think of themselves.
Room Manager: Haha, it's really pathetic, isn't it?

Room Manager: This is probably the last time I'll get to
talk to someone like this.

Room Manager: Lastly, if it's not too much trouble, if you
ever see her, please tell her,
Room Manager: "I had fun, thank you."
